Where you'll be working

Reporting to the Chief Health Officer, Health Protection NSW (HPNSW) is responsible for surveillance and public health response in NSW including collecting and managing and maintaining data systems for notifiable conditions, monitoring the epidemiology of notifiable conditions and taking appropriate action to prevent, control and minimise the impact of these conditions. It also provides public health advice and response to environmental issues affecting human health.

The Epidemiology Data and System (EDS) branch focuses on creating and managing sustainable data systems, and provides epidemiological data, information, intelligence and expert advice to support an effective public health response across the Public Health Network and to inform and evaluate public health policy in relation to conditions notifiable under the Public Health Act and emerging conditions of public health importance. The Branch works in close collaboration with Health Protection NSW branches.

For more information go to www.health.nsw.gov.au

About This Role

The Senior Data Analyst is located in Health Protection NSW (HPNSW), within the EDS Branch. The Senior Data Analyst is responsible for managing of data acquisition and wrangling processes, providing operational intelligence and real-time situational analysis, and preparing and providing data to external agencies.

The Senior Data Analyst will make a significant contribution to provision of high quality, reliable data and information for NSW Health and intergovernmental agencies through managing the acquisition of notifiable conditions and related data from a range of sources, enhancing and maintaining data wrangling processes, and preparing data for use of reporting, in a high scrutiny environment. The Senior Data Analyst will manage data analysts as required, oversee work outputs of team members as directed and provide mentorship for junior team members. This position will also provide analytics advice to staff within EDS and across Health Protection.
